<p>Israel says Hamas has not returned the bodies of 19 Israeli hostages as required under a recent ceasefire, and sent a team into Gaza to assist searches for the remains [washingtonpost.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Hamas counters that many remains are trapped under rubble and that it needs specialist equipment to reach them, a claim Israeli officials dispute [bbc.com#1][theguardian.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1]. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vowed to increase pressure and discussed the impasse with President Trump, who separately warned Hamas over recent killings he said breached the deal [timesofisrael.com#1][france24.com#1][newarab.com#1]. Turkey has deployed disaster-relief specialists to help recover bodies in Gaza, offering practical support amid the standoff [france24.com#1][newarab.com#1]. While Washington has downplayed claims of an outright ceasefire breach, Israel maintains that failing to return the remains would violate the agreement [firstpost.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/xzqAJlF4TbWcd5eC2cwH0_H4c8WEEgZudoFvDud5ydGTF-oeAWFHZ2p7Dz3ayzXo0N2gcoip8XzPaKrcBmBKaIAQQ4MDWCfHZ3y6mdfWxbptPJx3DSzKVBOAcsqMc3R8bll4DZ_2MYRCBumL_icoED860V08FteY_U62ekhxM9k0GXebZ7rvMX1oCaDCZB3ddTsHRulsVHgMrl4aGKKvFTalm4ot4QiR7SdiHWxqRQ4lhYwYKOnsxC1yfnF3lmc0dw' alt='Turkish disaster-relief personnel prepare equipment amid efforts to recover bodies in Gaza.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Ceasefire terms: Israel argues the truce obligates Hamas to return all hostages’ remains, and non-compliance would breach the agreement [washingtonpost.com#1].</li><li>Families’ stance: The main captives’ families group urged Israel to pause further stages of the deal until all remains are returned [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Turkish deployment: A Turkish defense source said 81 AFAD personnel are in Gaza, including a dedicated team to locate bodies under rubble [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Aid bottlenecks: Despite the ceasefire, most restrictions on aid have persisted, throttling desperately needed supplies into Gaza [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Burials at home: As remains are recovered, funerals have been held in Israel while the search continues [washingtonpost.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Government of Israel: Netanyahu says Israel is determined to secure the return of all hostages and will continue pressuring Hamas. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gkm0243wzo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>Hamas: Hamas says the bodies it could access have been returned and that other remains are buried under rubble requiring specialized equipment. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gkm0243wzo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>United States: President Trump warned Hamas over recent killings that he said violated the ceasefire he helped broker. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20251017-turkey-recover-hostages-gaza-trump-hamas'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Turkey: Ankara deployed AFAD disaster specialists, including a team tasked with recovering bodies, to assist searches in Gaza. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/turkish-experts-help-find-bodies-gaza-trump-warns-hamas'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Captives’ families campaign group: They demanded Israel halt further stages of the agreement until all remains are returned. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/turkish-experts-help-find-bodies-gaza-trump-warns-hamas'>The New Arab</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/team-enters-gaza-to-search-for-hostages-bodies-as-israel-vows-to-ramp-up-pressure/'>Team enters Gaza to search for hostages’ bodies, as Israel vows to ramp up pressure</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c4gkm0243wzo'>Netanyahu &#x27;determined&#x27; to pressure Hamas to find remaining dead hostages</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/16/hamas-hostage-bodies-recovered-amid-israel-gaza-fighting-ceasefire-deal'>Israel an